message.content: cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB. The paper discusses an information retrieval technique for multi-hop question answering, which involves finding multiple supporting evidence to answer a question. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), or Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories of arXiv CS. Among these, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category as the paper specifically focuses on improving the retrieval process for multi-hop QA. The other sub-categories are also relevant as they involve techniques and methods that are commonly used in multi-hop QA.
